                <tr> <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="title" --> 
                  <td align="left" class="maintitle">Accommodation</td>
                  <!-- InstanceEndEditable --></tr>
                <tr> 
                  <td align="left" class="bodytext">&nbsp; </td>
                </tr>
                <tr> <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="main text" --> 
                  <td align="left" valign="top" class="bodytext"> <table width="100%"  border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="2" class="greypicbox">
                    
                  </table>                
                    <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5">
                      <tr>
                        <td width="30%" valign="top"><img src="images/accom01.jpg" alt="Hall of residence at Trinity &amp; All Saints  " width="113" height="113"></td>
                        <td width="70%" valign="middle" class="bodytext style1">Trinity &amp; All Saints has nine halls of residence on campus that provide catered or self-catered accommodation for most first year students. All rooms contain a bed, wardrobe, chair desk and wash basin. Some rooms in catered halls have en-suite facilities.</td>
                      </tr>
                    </table> 
                    <p>A new development of self-catering ensuite accommodation is currently under   construction. &nbsp;Each two storey unit will comprise six study bedrooms plus a   communal kitchen/dining area.&nbsp; We expect this accommodation to be ready for   September 2007. </p>
                    <table width="100%"  border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5">
                      <tr>
                        <td><img src="images/accom03.jpg" width="113" height="113"></td>
                        <td class="bodytext">We aim to provide accommodation for all first year students who apply for a room. Although we are unable to guarantee accommodation, we fully expect to accommodate all first year students who would like a room on campus</td>
                      </tr>
                    </table>                    
                    <p><strong>Applying for accommodation on campus</strong><br>
                    All undergraduate applicants holding a FIRM place with Leeds Trinity &amp; All Saints will be sent the Student Accommodation Guide 2007/08 and the Application Form for Halls of Residence, towards the end of May 2007.   You should fill in the application form and return it to the Accommodation Office as soon as possible.  This will be date stamped on receipt and will be used as the basis for allocating rooms on a &lsquo;first come first served&rsquo; principle. </p>
                    <p>You will be asked to indicate your preference for ensuite self-catering, standard self-catering, ensuite part catered or standard part catered.  We do our best to allocate your preferred type of accommodation, but some halls quickly become over-subscribed, in which case an alternative type may be offered.   </p>
                    <p>For students holding an insurance or clearing place with us, the information pack and application form are sent out once the place becomes firm (usually after A level results). </p>
                    <p>For any questions about accommodation at Trinity &amp; All Saints, please contact the Accommodation Office on (0113) 
                      283 7112 or email <a href="mailto:accommodation@leedstrinity.ac.uk">accommodation@leedstrinity.ac.uk</a>. Why not view our <a href="http://www.leedstrinity.ac.uk/360/ipix/accommodation.htm">Accommodation Virtual Tour</a>? </p>
                    <table width="100%"  border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5">
                      <tr>
                        <td height="133"><img src="images/accom02.jpg" width="113" height="113"></td>
                        <td class="bodytext"><p>The Accommodation office is open:<br>
                        10am &#8211; 12.15pm and 1.15 - 4pm  Mon to Thurs</p>
                        </td>
                      </tr>
                    </table>                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p><br>
                    </p>
